    "title": {
      "rendered": "Are the Majority of Online Donors Liberal Female Gen Xers?"
    },
    "content": {
      "rendered": "<p><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-21244\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/Majority-of-Online-Donors-Liberal-Female-Gen-X-Facebook-300x300.jpg?resize=300%2C300\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/Majority-of-Online-Donors-Liberal-Female-Gen-X-Facebook.jpg?resize=300%2C300&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/Majority-of-Online-Donors-Liberal-Female-Gen-X-Facebook.jpg?resize=150%2C150&amp;ssl=1 150w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/Majority-of-Online-Donors-Liberal-Female-Gen-X-Facebook.jpg?resize=200%2C200&amp;ssl=1 200w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/Majority-of-Online-Donors-Liberal-Female-Gen-X-Facebook.jpg?resize=75%2C75&amp;ssl=1 75w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/Majority-of-Online-Donors-Liberal-Female-Gen-X-Facebook.jpg?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" />Liberal female Gen Xers may not be the majority of online donors, but they definitely are the demographic participating most in the <a href=\"https://funraise.org/techreport-past-reports\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><strong>2017 Global Trends in Giving Survey</strong></a>. Good for them and <em>thank you</em>, however, the inaugural edition of the Global Trends in Giving Report to be released September 4, 2017 will only be as good as the data it represents.</p>\n<p><strong>We need more diversity in our survey respondents (!!)</strong> in terms of gender, age, political and religious affiliation, and geographical location. Whoever you are, where ever your are, if you have donated to a nonprofit within the last 12 months, then please volunteer 3-5 minutes of your time and participate in the survey. The survey is 100% anonymous and <strong>published\u00a0in English, espa\u00f1ol, and fran\u00e7ais</strong>.\u00a0As the\u00a0world&#8217;s first ever attempt to study individual giving on a global scale, nonprofits worldwide are hungry for data that represents\u00a0and speaks for the global donor community. <em><strong>Your participation is greatly appreciated.</strong></em></p>\n<p><center></center></p>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\">2017 Global Trends in Giving Survey Respondent Data<br />\n<em>(1,457 respondents as of May 19, 2017 &#8211; Survey closes June 30)</em></h2>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\">1. 60% of survey respondents identify as very liberal or somewhat liberal.</h2>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://givingreport.ngo/\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-21257\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/political-data-donors.jpg?resize=600%2C458\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"458\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/political-data-donors.jpg?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/political-data-donors.jpg?resize=300%2C229&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\">2. 76% of survey respondents are female.</h2>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://givingreport.ngo/\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-21258\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/gender-donors.jpg?resize=600%2C393\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"393\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/gender-donors.jpg?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/gender-donors.jpg?resize=300%2C197&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\">3. 34% of survey respondents are Gen Xers.</h2>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://givingreport.ngo/\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-21260\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/gen-x-donors-1.jpg?resize=600%2C509\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"509\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/gen-x-donors-1.jpg?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/gen-x-donors-1.jpg?resize=300%2C255&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\">4. 79% of survey participants chose online giving as one of two preferred methods of giving.</h2>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://givingreport.ngo/\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-21262\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/donor-data-1.jpg?resize=600%2C737\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"737\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/donor-data-1.jpg?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/donor-data-1.jpg?resize=244%2C300&amp;ssl=1 244w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\">5. 50% of the survey respondents live in the United States. 19% in Australia. 10% in Canada.</h2>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://givingreport.ngo/\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-21263\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/donors-by-country.jpg?resize=600%2C430\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"430\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/donors-by-country.jpg?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/donors-by-country.jpg?resize=300%2C215&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\">6. Of those that are inspired to give during religious holidays, 80% of survey respondents give during Christian holidays. 3% during\u00a0Jewish holidays. 2% during Buddhist holidays.</h2>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://givingreport.ngo/\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-21275\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/religion-impact-on-giving-1.jpg?resize=600%2C826\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"826\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/religion-impact-on-giving-1.jpg?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/religion-impact-on-giving-1.jpg?resize=218%2C300&amp;ssl=1 218w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n",
      "protected": false
    },
